How can I take an iCloud photo collection or album and make it shareable to this guy

2025-06-30T01:22:28.656639Z assistant

Heres how you can share an iCloud photo collection or album directly with Pete (or anyone) from your iPhone or iPad:

If its a Shared Album:

If you already created a Shared Album, you can give Pete access like this:

  1. Open Photos.
  2. Go to the Albums tab scroll to Shared Albums tap the album.
  3. Tap the People icon (or "More" "Shared Album Details").
  4. Toggle Public Website to ON (this generates a public iCloud.com link).
  5. Tap Share Link choose how to send it (text, email, copy/paste it, etc.).

He doesnt need an Apple devicehe can view it from any browser.

If its NOT a Shared Album (just your normal camera roll or an existing album):

Option 1: Create a Shared Album

  1. Open Photos and select the images or videos you want to share.
  2. Tap the Share icon (box with arrow).
  3. Choose Add to Shared Album.
  4. Tap New Shared Album, give it a name (like "Evidence for Pete"), and tap Next.
  5. Skip inviting people (unless you want to invite by email).
  6. Once created, follow the steps above to make it a Public Website and share the link.

Option 2: Use a File Link (if you want him to download copies)

If he needs actual file downloads:

  1. Select the photos in Photos app.
  2. Tap Share choose Save to Files.
  3. Save them to iCloud Drive a folder like Evidence for Pete.
  4. Go to Files app long-press the folder tap Share.
  5. Choose Copy iCloud Link (or Share via Mail/Messages).
  6. Now he can view or download the files directly.

If youre on Mac or need help doing it from iCloud.com or another device, I can walk you through that too.
